HEADWORD: Escritoire
<hw>Es`cri*toire"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>escritoire</ets>, F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧critoire</ets>, LL.
<ets>scriptorium</ets>, fr. L. <ets>scriptorius</ets> belonging to
writing, fr. <ets>sribere</ets> to write. See <er>Script</er>, and cf.
<er>Scrutoire</er>.]</ety> <def>A piece of furniture used as a writing
table, commonly with drawers, pigeonholes, and the like; a secretary or
writing desk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

